.TH ISOCMD 1 "June 2026" "Iso Commander 7.2.1" "Iso-Commander Manual"

.SH NAME
Iso Commander (isocmd) \- A single binary command-line utility for managing .iso files and converting image formats.

.SH DESCRIPTION
Iso Commander (isocmd) is a single binary command-line utility for managing .iso files and converting various image formats to .iso using multi-threaded processing.

.SH NON-INTERACTIVE COMMANDS
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-version
Show program version.
.TP
.B \-\-silent
Suppress informational, error and warning output.
.TP
.B \-d\fIN\fR
Max recursion depth when scanning for ISOs (default: unlimited).
.TP
.B mount
Mount one or more ISO files or directories containing ISOs (requires root).
.TP
.B umount | unmount
Unmount ISO mount points; without arguments or with \fBall\fR, unmounts all under /mnt (requires root).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TS
tab(@);
lb l.
isocmd /path/to/file1.iso /path/to/file2.iso mount@Mount specific ISOs
isocmd /path/to/dir mount@Mount all ISOs in a directory
isocmd \-d2 /path/to/dir mount@Mount ISOs up to depth 2
isocmd \-\-silent /path/to/file.iso mount@Mount silently
isocmd /mnt/iso_example /mnt/iso_other umount@Unmount specific mount points
isocmd \-\-silent /mnt/iso_example umount@Unmount specific mount point silently
isocmd umount@Unmount all ISO mount points
isocmd \-\-silent umount@Unmount all silently
.TE

.SH UI INTERACTIVE OPTIONS AND FEATURES
.TP
.B ManageISO
Mount, unmount, delete, move, copy, and write ISO files to USB (bootable preserved). Requires root for mount/umount/write2usb.

.TP
.B Convert2ISO
Ported from original C tools and utilizes libchdr.
.br
Converts .bin, .img, .chd, .daa, .gbi, .mdf, and .nrg files to .iso.
.br
.sp
.B ccd2iso
(GPL-2.0 or later, Danny Kurniawan and Kerry Harris) \(em converts CloneCD .bin/.img disc images.
.br
.B mdf2iso
(GPL-2.0 or later, Salvatore Santagati) \(em converts Alcohol 120% .mdf disc images.
.br
.B nrg2iso
(GPL-3.0 or later, Grégory Kokanosky) \(em converts Nero Burning ROM .nrg disc images.
.br
.B daa2iso
(GPL-2.0 or later, Luigi Auriemma) \(em converts PowerISO .daa and gBurner .gbi disc images.
.br
.B libchdr
(BSD-3-Clause, MAME project, Romain TISSERAND) \(em decodes Compressed Hunks of Data (.chd) images.
.TP

.B ImportISO
Creates and updates a local ISO database. The database has a maximum file size limit of \fB1MB\fR.

.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file is located at \fI~/.config/isocmd/config\fR and uses a \fIkey = value\fR format.
.SS THEME
.TS
tab(@);
l l l.
skin  Accent color for menus and headers@green|cyan|white|purple|amber|rose|gray (Default: white)
theme Color palette for lists and prompts@original|classic|high_contrast|neon|ocean|sunset|forest|
@midnight|mono|retro|crimson|dracula|tokyo|paper|sakura (Default: original)
.TE
.SS GENERAL
.TS
tab(@);
lb l l.
auto_update@Enable background metadata updates on startup@on|off (Default: off)
filenames_only@Show filenames instead of full paths; global override except unmount list@on|off (Default: off)
pagination@Items per page (0 to disable)@integer >= 0 (Default: 25)
.TE
.SS HISTORY
.TS
tab(@);
lb l l.
folder_path_history_lines@Max unique folder paths to persist (0 to disable)@integer (Default: 30)
filter_history_lines@Max unique search filters to persist (0 to disable)@integer (Default: 15)
.TE
.SS DISPLAY
Controls whether lists are shown in \fBfull\fR (detailed) or \fBcompact\fR format.
If \fBfilenames_only\fR is enabled, path details are stripped regardless of these settings.
.PP
.TS
tab(@);
lb lb.
List@Default
_
mount_list@compact
umount_list@full
cp_mv_rm_list@full
write2usb_list@compact
convert2iso_lists@compact

.TE
.SS THREADS
Iso Commander uses a static central thread pool (size = min(hardware_threads, combined_thread_cap)).
.br
Sub-limits draw from this pool; tasks queue if the pool is full.
.PP
.TS
tab(@);
lb l.
combined_thread_cap@Global thread pool limit (Default: 16, takes effect on restart)
thread_cap_for_mount@Max concurrent mounting tasks (Default: 8)
thread_cap_for_umount@Max concurrent unmounting tasks (Default: 8)
thread_cap_for_cp_mv@Max concurrent copy/move tasks (Default: 4)
thread_cap_for_rm@Max concurrent file removal tasks (Default: 8)
thread_cap_for_convert2iso@Max concurrent ISO conversions (Default: 4)
thread_cap_for_database_cleanup@Max concurrent threads for ISO database cleanup (Default: 4)
thread_cap_for_list_sorting@Max concurrent threads for UI list sorting (Default: 2)
thread_cap_for_list_filtering@Max concurrent threads for UI list filtering (Default: 2)
.TE

.SH FILES
.I Note: If run with sudo, these paths are relative to /root/ instead of the user's home directory.
.TP
.I ~/.config/isocmd/config
Primary configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/isocmd/database/iso_commander_database.txt
Main ISO metadata database.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/isocmd/database/iso_commander_path_database.txt
Persistent history of accessed folder paths.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/isocmd/database/iso_commander_filter_database.txt
Persistent history of search filter terms.

